public static record IAnimatedBlockRecoveryData.AnimatedBlockRecoveryData(org.bukkit.World world, Vector3Di position, org.bukkit.block.data.BlockData data) extends Record implements IAnimatedBlockRecoveryData
Represents an object that stores recovery data for an animated block.

The recovery data consists of the world, position, and block data of the block that needs to be recovered.

The recovery action is performed by placing the block data at the specified position in the specified world.

    • recover

      public boolean recover()
      Description copied from interface: IAnimatedBlockRecoveryData
      Attempts recovery of the animated block display.

      This method gives the animated block the opportunity to recover from a crash or other unexpected event.

      No guarantees are made about the exact behavior of this method, but as long as any kind of recovery action is performed, this method should return true. Only when this method is a no-op should it return false.

      Specified by:
      recover in interface IAnimatedBlockRecoveryData
      Returns:
      True if a recovery action was performed, false otherwise.
